The Kebbi State governor, Senator Abubakar Atiku Bagudu has approved the commencement of free registration of applicants for the federal government’s N-Power programme for the unemployed youths across the state. This was announced in Birnin Kebbi by the commissioner of Budget and Economic Planning, Dr. Abba Sani Kalgo. The free N-Power registration programme, according to the Commissioner, would commence on Monday, July 6th, 2020, at all the designated centers, which include all the local government areas and Emirate Headquarters. He further explained that the applicants from the state capital, Birnin Kebbi, would be registered at the Emir of Gwandu’s Palace, Alhaji Muhammadu Iliyasu Bashar and ICT Centre of the Waziri Umaru Federal Polytechnic, Birnin Kebbi. He averred, “Kebbi State ministry of Budget and Planning is calling on Youths interested in the federal government’s N-Power programme to hurry up and come for the free registration and additional information on the programme at the centres provided throughout the state”. ”The registration starts on Monday, 6th July, 2020, throughout the centres provided. Interested youths are to come with their BVN document and valid identity card.